summary: What’s the deal with Toe? Has he been kicked to the curb yet?
question: What’s the deal with Toe? Has he been kicked to the curb yet?
answer: Yes and no I think? After two and a half months of basically nothing, I would be somewhat surprised if she starts being seen with him again. However, I don’t think he‘ll be fully dropped (as in Tree issuing an article saying so) until after she‘s out. It seems like both girls are trying to legitimize their relationships (Taylor just by keeping him around, Karlie by being loud with Josh) before big things happen for Taylor. That being said, I understand why this may be the plan, but it doesn’t stop me from worrying about folks in the GP who might accuse her of coming out for attention. A majority of the public isn’t locked into Taylor’s every move so this is going to come out of left field for a lot of people. That’s why I keep saying I hope she’s able to reallyyyy explain herself. I don’t want people to have any “comebacks” and I want her to just be able to enjoy the moment. If anyone can get through to these people though, it’s her.

summary: taylor swift helped me come out
body:
taylor swift helped me come out

lol this is a story i’ve never told before

when 1989 first came out i was blown away by how different but amazing it was and i fell in love with it. i’ve been a swiftie since TOMG but 1989 just changed me entirely. 

when i heard welcome to new york for the first time i had no idea that it would change my life several years later.

it’s been a year since i came out to my mum as bisexual and hearing taylor say that “you can want who you want/boys and boys and girls and girl” it just stuck with me in a way i didn’t even know yet. it really helped me feel comfortable with who i am and feel confident enough in sharing it with my mum, who literally went “okay” and left it. 

flash forward to now, a year after coming out to my mum, and ME! is making me feel even more comfortable in my own skin and body. I’m loving myself for the first time in years and singing that im fun and the only one of me. 

if i ever get to meet taylor there are a million things i want to thank her for, but i think the self love is the main one. taylor has absolutely changed my life and i will defend her for literally forever. 

i will hug her one day and i will tell her thank you for everything.
